column5: I'm going up to Lake Dinorwic east of Dryden this year. Has anyone had experience with the lake and could help me finding some good spots to nail some walleyes.

:D Just West of Hubers Lodge passed the weed bed around the 8ft-12ft mark and EAst of Hubers around first marker by the rocks can be awesome. We also did well around Moose Bay. If you want the best smallie fishing, go all the way to the southern tip by the waterfall and portage a couple hundred feet to Peak Lake.Have a great time.
